############## ENGLISH #####################################################

This archive includes issue number 6 of Amiga on Line (tm) 
April 1997, Amiga on Line is the first italian WEB-magazine for Amiga 
games, but it's also full english.
In Amiga on line number 6 you can find:

-Going on paper : Amiga On Line gets published.

        NEWS:

-Amy Tech sold,
-Myst finally announced,
-Islona,
-Albion on Amiga,
-TFX returns,
-World of Amiga show,
-Master Axe released,
-Applaud Software,
-Another browser,
-Another game from Mutation.


        PREVIEWS:

-Aurora Works letter to AOL,

-Alien Formula 1,
-Ffigy,
-Flyin' High,
-Genetic Species,
-Max Rally,
-Quake,
-Strangers,
-Trapped 2.

        REVIEWS:

-XP8 ECS,
-Uropa 2.

-A Special on new BUDGET releases.

And also our Tips section, our HOT Links and the reader's Top Ten.

Number 7 (May 1997) will be avaible on-line from 15 May 1997 and 
will include Master Axe and Blockhead review, previews of Marbelous, Kargon, 
Testament, Castle Kingdoms and a lot of more.

